# State Charity Bureau Annual Report

Produce a filing-ready annual report for state charitable solicitation regulators with verified state-specific requirements.

## Prerequisites

1. Filing state and regulator (charity bureau/AG/Secretary of State)
2. Reporting period start/end and fiscal year end
3. Organization legal name, EIN, charity registration number, and principal address
4. IRS Form 990/990-EZ/990-PF and financial statements for the period
5. Board/officer roster with titles, terms, and compensation
6. Fundraising methods and any professional fundraiser/solicitor/co-venturer contracts
7. Prior state charity filings and correspondence, if available

## Output Structure / Process

### Output Mode

| Mode | Use When | Output |
|---|---|---|
| Full Compliance Package | Default filing-ready narrative | Report sections, tables, exhibits index, certification, signatures, filing instructions |
| Form-Field Mode | State form or portal requires field-by-field responses | Field answers with citations and optional narrative addendum |
| Executive Briefing | Board/leadership review before filing | 2-3 page compliance summary and open items |

### Intake Defaults

| Item | Default | Label |
|---|---|---|
| Filing type | Annual charitable solicitation renewal report | [ASSUMED] if not confirmed |
| Reporting period | Most recent completed 12-month fiscal year | [ASSUMED] if not confirmed |
| Accounting basis | Accrual if 990/FS indicate accrual; otherwise as provided | [ASSUMED] if not confirmed |
| Professional fundraisers | None | [ASSUMED] if not confirmed |
| Multi-state solicitations | Address only requested state | Note if other states indicated |
| Audit threshold | Determine via state research | [TO BE CONFIRMED] if unknown |

### Open Items

| # | Item | Status |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Filing state/jurisdiction | [OPEN] |
| 2 | Legal name, EIN, charity registration # | [OPEN] |
| 3 | Reporting period dates | [OPEN] |
| 4 | Total revenue for threshold tier | [OPEN] |
| 5 | Professional fundraiser/solicitor/co-venturer use | [OPEN] |
| 6 | Output mode | [OPEN] |
| 7 | Mandatory form or portal | [OPEN] |

### State Requirements Research

- Use official sources only: regulator site, statutes, admin code, official instructions
- Record each rule with source and last-updated date
- If sources conflict, mark [CONFLICT - VERIFY WITH COUNSEL]
- If a rule is not confirmed, mark [TO BE CONFIRMED]
- Mark uncertain statutory citations as [VERIFY]

**State Requirements Matrix**

